<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Italian distribution of reared parasitoids.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
Apulia: 
<bibRefCitation author="Nuzzaci, G" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica" pageId="23" pageNumber="90" pagination="47 - 52" title="Notes on the biocenosis in Puglia of Lobesia (Polychrosis) botrana (Schiff.) (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) exclusive to Daphnegnidium L." volume="17" year="1982">Nuzzaci and Triggiani 1982</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aleiodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aleiodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aleiodes</taxonomicName>
Wesmael, 1838, is a cosmopolitan genus of 240 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, DSK" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="25" pageNumber="92" title="Home of Ichneumonoidea" url="http://www.taxapad.com/" year="1997 - 2012">Yu 1997-2012</bibRefCitation>
), with 42 of them listed in Europe (Fauna Europaea).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="84" type="host">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="84">Host range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="84">
In most cases, the species of this genus live on larvae of macrolepidoptera, both diurnal and nocturnal and, to a lesser extent, on larvae of microlepidoptera, including tortricids. They are koinobiont larval endoparasitoids, and lay their eggs in the host young larva and pupate inside the mummified remains of the dead caterpillar. Three species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aleiodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aleiodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aleiodes</taxonomicName>
are associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Lobesia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lobesia botrana" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botrana">Lobesia botrana</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nuzzaci, G" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica" pageId="23" pageNumber="90" pagination="47 - 52" title="Notes on the biocenosis in Puglia of Lobesia (Polychrosis) botrana (Schiff.) (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) exclusive to Daphnegnidium L." volume="17" year="1982">Nuzzaci and Triggiani (1982)</bibRefCitation>
obtained a single specimen of an unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aleiodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aleiodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aleiodes</taxonomicName>
by EGVM larvae living on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Thymelaeaceae" genus="Daphne" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Daphne gnidium" order="Malvales" pageId="17" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gnidium">Daphne gnidium</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
